Red Sox’ Ellsbury, Cardinals’ Berkman Win Comeback Player of Year Awards

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-10-13T18:35:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/red-sox-ellsbury-cardinals-berkman-win-comeback-player-of-year-awards.html
Jacoby Ellsbury of the Boston Red
Sox and Lance Berkman of the  St. Louis Cardinals  won  Major
League Baseball ’s Comeback Player of the Year Awards.  Ellsbury, Boston’s 28-year-old center fielder, hit .321
with 32 home runs, 105 runs batted in and 119 runs scored. After
being limited to 18 games because of injuries in 2010, Ellsbury
this year joined Vladimir Guerrero, Alfonso Soriano and Alex Rodriguez as the only players in history with more than 200
hits, 100 RBI, 35 steals and 30 homers in a season.  Berkman, 35, hit .301 with 31 homers and 94 RBI while
playing outfield and first base for the Cardinals. In 2010, he
hit a combined .248 with 14 home runs and 58 RBI for the Houston
Astros and  New York Yankees .  The awards are voted on by the 30 team beat reporters for
 MLB.com , the official website of Major League Baseball.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
